I encountered a problem where I need to put numbers into a set, and later check whether a number is contained in the set. But since we are using Set&lt;Long&gt;, an idea crossed my mind: will 1 equal to 1? &ndash; If I create two Long object holding the same value, are they consider equal by Set?
Yes. Because the hashcode method is implemeted as follows:
return (int)(value ^ (value &gt;&gt;&gt; 32));  So only the value of that Number object matters, as opposed to the &ldquo;regular&rdquo; implementation:
